  "prompt": "What is the Nirvana song \"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" about?",
  "response": "\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" by Nirvana is widely interpreted as a critique of the apathy and disillusionment felt by Generation X, the generation born roughly between the early 1960s and early 1980s. Written by Kurt Cobain, the band's lead vocalist and guitarist, the song features lyrics that are often viewed as a commentary on the superficiality and aimlessness of teenage life. The song's title itself was inspired by a phrase written on Cobain's wall by his friend Kathleen Hanna, which referred to a brand of deodorant called \"Teen Spirit.\"\n\nMusically, the song blends aggressive guitar riffs with grunge aesthetics, capturing the raw energy and rebellious spirit associated with Nirvana's style. The song became an anthem of the youth and played a significant role in bringing grunge music into the mainstream in the early 1990s. Although Cobain himself had mixed feelings about the song's success, \"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" remains one of Nirvana\u2019s most iconic tracks and a defining song of the era.",
